 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "MarketEntry-LLM ⊣ Market-Entry Compliance Governor, a REAL compiled
 `kotoba-lang/langgraph` StateGraph (`:intake -> :advise -> :govern ->
 :decide -+-> :commit / :request-approval -> :commit / :hold`), with a
 real `interrupt-before #{:request-approval}` + in-memory checkpointer
 pausing every `:jurisdiction/assess`/`:filing/draft`/`:filing/submit`
 for human sign-off, and both `:commit` and `:hold` durably appending
 to the audit ledger. `marketentry.facts` catalogs the Republic of
 Botswana (BWA) market-entry surface, grounded in primary-text fetches
 of the Public Procurement Act, 2021 (No. 24 of 2021), the Companies
 Act (CAP 42:01, CIPA), the Botswana Unified Revenue Service Act (CAP
 53:03) and Income Tax Act (CAP 52:01), and BITC's own site -- and
 EXPLICITLY disambiguates Botswana's own Public Procurement Regulatory
 Authority (PPRA, the s.6 continuation of the former PPADB) from
 Kenya's and Pakistan's identically-acronymed, unrelated national
 regulators of the same name (`marketentry.facts/ppra-reference-
 disambiguated?` is a regression guard against this exact
 fabrication trap). Seven governor checks (spec-basis ·
 evidence-incomplete (CIPA registration + BURS TIN + Contractors'
 Register) · reservation-ineligible against the Public Procurement
 Act, 2021 s.76(1)/s.78(1) citizen-reservation preference scale, the
 flagship ORDERED TIER-CLASSIFICATION check shape for this vertical ·
 engagement-fee-mismatch · TIN-registration-unverified (BURS) ·
 BITC/BOSSC facilitation-unacknowledged, entity-scope-gated to a
 foreign-owned engagement, a FACILITATION gate that never substitutes
 for the CIPA registration check · already-drafted/already-submitted
 double-actuation guards), all HARD and unoverridable;
 `:filing/draft`/`:filing/submit` are permanently absent from every
 phase's `:auto` set (never auto-commit, at any phase, by construction
 -- two independent layers, `marketentry.governor`'s high-stakes gate
 and `marketentry.phase`'s phase table, agree). Store gained a
 `DatomicStore` via `kotoba-lang/langchain-store` (no hand-rolled
 EDN-blob codec), proven ≡ `MemStore` by a store-contract test. 30+
 tests across governor contract (including a dedicated PPRA-
 disambiguation regression test and a BITC-gate-fires-only-for-
 foreign-owned-engagements test), phase invariants, store parity,
 registry conformance and facts coverage, clj-kondo 0 errors."}
